com.beepell.expression
Class PropertyAliasQuery

java.lang.Object
  com.beepell.expression.XPathExpression
      com.beepell.expression.PropertyAliasQuery

public class PropertyAliasQuery
extends XPathExpression

Property Aliases may contain a query. The result of the query is expected to be of the type assigned in the Property. The property alias itself is also typed to indicate which type of variables that the alias may apply.

The query expression is static and applied to different variables of the indicated type. If this is a message type (which applies for all message variables of that type) then a part MUST be specified. Type, part and namespace context is also static.

Author:
Tim Hallwyl

Create a Property Alias Query Expression.

If expression is null, the context node is returned as if no query where part of the alias.

Parameters:
type - the message schema type
part - the part of the message, that the query applies.
expression - the query expression to apply.
namespaceContext - the namespace context of the property alias query expression.
